              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Place it on the most relevant blog posts, build a dedicated landing page, share on social channels, and add it to email signatures. Blog-to-lead-magnet pathways generate the highest organic volume because the reader's intent is already aligned.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How many lead magnets should a website have?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>At minimum, one per major topic cluster. A marketing agency should maintain separate magnets for SEO, social media, and email marketing. The goal is topical relevance: one download per intent, not one for the whole site.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How long should a lead magnet form be?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Request only what you need — usually email address and first name. Each additional field reduces conversion by roughly 10%. For high-value offers (consultations, audits) it is reasonable to ask for company name and website since the intent is already high.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a lead magnet and a content upgrade?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A lead magnet is a standalone asset available site-wide. A content upgrade is a lead magnet built specifically for one post — for example, a checklist version of a single article. Content upgrades typically convert higher because of the exact match to the reader's intent.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

